  "templates": [
    {
      "id": 1226,
      "guid": "8d726a12-1f93-48e9-8609-196737ce0560",
      "name": "VMware vCenter / ESXi Monitoring",
      "comments": "Monitors a VMware vCenter (or standalone ESXi) environment through the NetXMS agent 'vcenter' extension.\n\nThe extension polls vCenter on its own timer and serves all data from an in-memory cache, so DCI polling never hits vCenter directly.\n\nInstance discovery uses the agent lists VMware.VMList, VMware.DatastoreList and VMware.HostList. \nThe instance key is the managed-object ID (MOID), which is stable across renames. \nEach DCI carries an instance filter that resolves the human-readable name via the VMware.{VM,Datastore,Host}.Name metric and exposes it as {instance-name}, falling back to the MOID if the name cannot be read. \n\nAlarm lifecycle is self-contained: every threshold raises a template-owned VMW_* event (separate warning and critical events per metric, so the alarm severity matches the level reached) and clears via VMW_THRESHOLD_CLEARED through dedicated create and terminate event-processing rules keyed on VMW_THRESHOLD_%i_<dciId>_<instance>, so alarms close correctly without relying on the built-in threshold rules.\n",
      "exclusionGroup": "",
      "path": [
        "VMware"
      ],
